nodes.bodyText:
I'm pretty sure there is a race here.  The task could finish between this check and creating the listener below, and in that case the listener may never be notified.  If you call createNewListener() before this check, I believe it will eliminate the race.  Something like:
CompletableFuture<?> listener = taskStatusVersionChange.createNewListener();
if (callersCurrentVersion < taskStatusVersion.get() || taskHolderReference.get().isFinished()) {
    listener.cancel(true);
    return immediateFuture(getTaskStatus());
}
return Futures.transform(listener, input -> getTaskStatus(), directExecutor());

